narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Went over more basic seamanship and naval platforms.
It's Navigation 2.0 with some additional operational stuff thrown in closer to the end of the course.

This course was essentially a review of the content of intro to naval science and navigation plus a couple new things - overall I just got better at some of my weak points from earlier courses like moboards

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Material is not connected and requires a lot of memorization but the instructor was succinct and efficient with our time. I would cite him as the greatest strength of the course.
I don't really understand why we learn Navigation at all as freshmen if we will learn it again as seniors. But this course was well-structured and interesting enough.

strengths - good teaching, fair material

weaknesses - there could be more timely communication about quiz dates

comments: I mean, if you wanna take it then go for it
